      • setProtocolData

        public void setProtocolData​(java.lang.Object protocolData)
        Description copied from interface: com.genesyslab.platform.commons.protocol.runtime.CodecSupport
        Set arbitrary protocol specific data. It is used then to initialize codecs upon their creation. It is highly recommended to implement the protocolData object as set of interfaces that in turn provide access to codec specific data. Do not assume protocolData as an object for a single codec, since it will be impossible to extend such object. Such extending can be required if the protocol uses several codecs with external data and need to initialize them all with single object.
        Wrong: CodecData data = (CodecData) protocolData;
        Right: CodecData data = ((CodecDataHolder) protocolData).getCodecData(); Please, consult codecs documentation for additional information.
        Specified by:
        setProtocolData in interface com.genesyslab.platform.commons.protocol.runtime.CodecSupport
        Parameters:
        protocolData - protocol specific data.
        See Also:
        CustomTypeCodec
